/* Language */ Straightened out citation that mixes metadata from Faruqi's 2001 book and the 2003 chapter he wrote for Pollock's Literary Cultures in History. I've used the latter because it's a bit clearer.

Per [[MOS:FOREIGNITALIC]], make sparing use of native script. In the 5 sources cited, only one name is given in non-Latin script, the rest are unsupported back-transliterations by one or more editors (Mydust?). Wikipedia, as a tertiary source, should be giving readers a high level overview, not spelling out every detail. For all the variations of Hind/Hindustan, it's sufficient to link to [[Hindustan]], where the etymology is explained. Distinguish between chapter author and volume editor.

/* Astronomy */ The source says 86 Zijes were *available*, but doesn't break down how many were brought from abroad vs. produced locally. It says "some indigenous ones were also produced". Reduced overlinking per [[WP:Linking]]. The source attributes the claim, so Wikipedia should too, absent evidence that it's a widely held view.

Merging [[:Category:1570s in the Mughal Empire]] to [[:Category:16th century in the Mughal Empire]] and [[:Category:1570s in India]] per [[Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2024 April 5#16th century in the Mughal Empire]]
